    "subtask_body": "Final verification and minor TSP refinement. Let me check a few more 2-opt moves on the TSP tour.\n\nCurrent tour: [0,11,7,8,18,16,15,2,12,14,1,6,19,13,5,17,10,3,9,4]\nKey long edges: 18\u219216 (~45), 4\u21920 (~41.8), 10\u21923 (~34), 11\u21927 (~29.5), 2\u219212 (~31.4)\n\nTry reversing segment [16,15,2,12,14,1,6,19,13,5,17,10,3,9,4] - no that's the whole back half.\n\nTry: swap 16 position. 18(1,48)\u219216(2,3): dist=45. What if 16 goes between 15 and 2? Tour: 0,11,7,8,18,15,16,2,12,14,1,6,19,13,5,17,10,3,9,4. 18\u219215: sqrt(1521+2025)\u224859.5. Worse.\n\nTry: 0,11,7,8,18,16,2,15,12,14,1,6,19,13,5,17,10,3,9,4. 16\u21922: sqrt(900+144)\u224832.3, 2\u219215: sqrt(64+144)\u224814.4, 15\u219212: sqrt(289+961)\u224835.4. vs 16\u219215: 38, 15\u21922: 14.4, 2\u219212: 31.4. Old=83.8, New=82.1. Slight improvement.\n\nTry: 0,11,7,8,18,16,2,15,12,14,1,6,19,13,5,17,10,3,9,4. Let me also check 9\u21924\u21920 vs alternatives. 9(55,77)\u21924(57,60)\u21920(17,72): 17.1+41.8=58.9. vs 9\u21920: 40.3, 4 inserted elsewhere. Hard to improve without full solver.\n\nSteiner: confirmed 59 is optimal among simple trees. CJS: baseline 155 kept.",
    "subtask_id": 3,
